US Coast Guard captured the images of the James McBride and Rising Sun wrecks on the bottom of the Great Lake in the Manitou Passage . 
  The lake is home to dozens of shipwrecks due to the unpredictable weather . 
  The James Mc Bride ran aground in October 1857 and the Rising Sun crashed in October 1917 . 
  The images were taken by a helicopter during a routine patrol of the lake . 
  The wrecks were exposed by ice-melt on the lake and revealed by plankton in the water . 
 